根據{{link-en|挪威法律|Law of Norway}}<ref>[{{Cite web |url=http://m.db.no/2014/08/09/nyheter/utenriks/usa/forlik/penger/34699224/ |title={{lang|no|Forsikringsselskap utbetalte forlik på 130 000 kroner i småmynt|nocat=y}} |access-date=2020-02-23 |archive-date=2016-05-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507005205/http://m.db.no/2014/08/09/nyheter/utenriks/usa/forlik/penger/34699224/ |dead-url=no }} {{lang|no|Forsikringsselskap utbetalte forlik på 130 000 kroner i småmynt|nocat=y}}]</ref>，每次現金交易時使用25個或以內的硬幣，均具有[[法償|法償]]，視為合法交易，受付方不可拒收。

過往1克朗和5克朗的硬幣均刻有在任君主哈拉爾五世的肖像，但自近1997年起這兩款硬幣已改以徽號和聖奧拉夫動章代替。而皇室[[格言|格言]]「一切為了挪威」（{{lang|no|Alt for Norge}}）則在10克朗的正面上出現。

<!--
===Use of 10 Syrian pound coins in Norway===
The characteristics of the 10 [[Syrian_pound|Syrian pound]] (10 SYP) coin have been found to so closely resemble the 20 Norwegian kroner (20 NOK) coin that it can [[Slug_(coin)|fool vending machines, coins-to-cash machines, arcade machines, and any other coin-operated, automated service machine]] in the country. Whilst they are hardly similar to the naked eye, machines are unable to tell the coins apart, owing to their almost identical weight and size.

As of mid February 2017, 10 Syrian pounds were worth 39 øre, making the 20-kroner coin 51.5 times more valuable than the 10-pound coin. While not easy to find in Norway, the Syrian coins are still used in automated machines there with such frequency that {{lang|no|[[Posten_(Norway)|Posten Norge]]}}, the Norwegian postal service, decided to close many of their coins-to-cash machines on 18 February 2006, with plans to develop a system able to differentiate between the two coins. In the summer of 2005, a Norwegian man was sentenced to 30 days, [[suspended_sentence|suspended]], for having used Syrian coins in arcade machines in the [[municipalities_of_Norway|municipality]] of [[Bærum|Bærum]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/2006/02/18/458229.html |title=Myntsvindlere herjer i Oslo |first=Øystein |last=Andersen |work=[[Dagbladet|Dagbladet]] |publisher=DB Medialab AS |date=18 February 2006 |accessdate=8 March 2008 |language=Norwegian }}</ref>-->

===紙幣===
挪威銀行已於2017年起推出了第八代的通用鈔票，最後一款（1000克朗）亦已於2019年11月14日正式推出，整套鈔票的主題都和[[海洋|海洋]]有關<ref>[https://www.norges-bank.no/en/topics/notes-and-coins/New-banknote-series/On-the-choice-of-theme-and-motifs/ On the choice of theme and motifs] {{Wayback|url=https://www.norges-bank.no/en/topics/notes-and-coins/New-banknote-series/On-the-choice-of-theme-and-motifs/ |date=20210307214640 }}，挪威銀行網頁，2016年11月22日。</ref>。正面為主題圖案，背面則以[[抽象|抽象]]方塊和線條展現主題。至於第七代鈔票，除1000克朗仍可於2020年11月14日前使用外，其餘四款已不被視作合法貨幣，必須於10年免費更換期內到挪威銀行進行更換<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.norges-bank.no/en/topics/notes-and-coins/New-banknote-series/When-will-the-banknotes-be-launched/ |title=挪威銀行有關新舊鈔票轉換事宜。 |access-date=2020-02-23 |archive-date=2021-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307222115/https://www.norges-bank.no/en/topics/notes-and-coins/New-banknote-series/When-will-the-banknotes-be-launched/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

